BytesReceived: int; The number of bytes sent from the origin to the client during the network session.
BytesSent: int; The number of bytes sent from the client to the origin during the network session.
ClientTCPHandshakeDurationMs: int; Duration of handshaking the TCP connection between the client and Cloudflare in milliseconds.
ClientTLSCipher: string; TLS cipher suite used in the connection between the client and Cloudflare.
ClientTLSHandshakeDurationMs: int; Duration of handshaking the TLS connection between the client and Cloudflare in milliseconds.
ClientTLSVersion: string; TLS protocol version used in the connection between the client and Cloudflare.
ConnectionCloseReason: string; The reason for closing the connection, only applicable for TCP. Possible values are CLIENT_CLOSED | CLIENT_IDLE_TIMEOUT | CLIENT_TLS_ERROR | CLIENT_ERROR | ORIGIN_CLOSED | ORIGIN_TLS_ERROR | ORIGIN_ERROR | ORIGIN_UNREACHABLE | PROXY_CONN_REFUSED | UNKNOWN | MISMATCHED_IP_VERSIONS.
ConnectionReuse: bool; Whether the TCP connection was reused for multiple HTTP requests.
DestinationTunnelID: string; Identifier of the Cloudflare One connector to which the network session was routed to, if any, such as Cloudflare Tunnel or WARP device.
DetectedProtocol: string; Detected traffic protocol of the network session.
DeviceID: string; Identifier of the client device which initiated the network session, if applicable, (for example, WARP Device ID).
DeviceName: string; Name of the client device which initiated the network session, if applicable, (for example, WARP Device ID).
EgressColoName: string; The name of the Cloudflare colo from which traffic egressed to the origin.
EgressIP: string; Source IP used when egressing traffic from Cloudflare to the origin.
EgressPort: int; Source port used when egressing traffic from Cloudflare to the origin.
EgressRuleID: string; Identifier of the egress rule that was applied by the Secure Web Gateway, if any.
EgressRuleName: string; The name of the egress rule that was applied by the Secure Web Gateway, if any.
Email: string; Email address associated with the user identity which initiated the network session.
IngressColoName: string; The name of the Cloudflare colo to which traffic ingressed.
Offramp: string; The type of destination to which the network session was routed. Possible values are INTERNET | MAGIC | CFD_TUNNEL | WARP.
OriginIP: string; The IP of the destination ("origin") for the network session.
OriginPort: int; The port of the destination origin for the network session.
OriginTLSCertificateIssuer: string; The issuer of the origin TLS certificate.
OriginTLSCertificateValidationResult: string; The result of validating the TLS certificate of the origin. Possible values are VALID | EXPIRED | REVOKED | HOSTNAME_MISMATCH | NONE | UNKNOWN.
OriginTLSCipher: string; TLS cipher suite used in the connection between Cloudflare and the origin.
OriginTLSHandshakeDurationMs: int; Duration of handshaking the TLS connection between Cloudflare and the origin in milliseconds.
OriginTLSVersion: string; TLS protocol version used in the connection between Cloudflare and the origin.
Protocol: string; Network protocol used for this network session. Possible values are TCP | UDP | ICMP | ICMPV6.
RuleEvaluationDurationMs: int; The duration taken by Secure Web Gateway applying applicable Network, HTTP, and Egress rules to the network session in milliseconds.
SessionEndTime: int or string; The network session end timestamp with nanosecond precision.
SessionID: string; The identifier of this network session.
SessionStartTime: int or string; The network session start timestamp with nanosecond precision.
SourceIP: string; Source IP of the network session.
SourceInternalIP: string; Local LAN IP of the device. Only available when connected via a GRE/IPsec tunnel on-ramp.
SourcePort: int; Source port of the network session.
UserID: string; User identity where the network session originated from. Only applicable for WARP device clients.
VirtualNetworkID: string; Identifier of the virtual network configured for the client.
